  "text": "PF McP-1 levels are not correlated to the drug given nor the volume of drained PF The exact molecular mechanism by which intrapleural delivery of t-PA increases the output volume of PF remains unknown. Lansley et al delivered fibrinolytics to the pleural space of mice and proposed that t-PA induces the intrapleural levels of MCP-1 and reported a correlation between the MCP-1 levels and the volume of pleural effusion. [CITATION_1] MCP-1 has been identified as a promoter of vascular permeability and an inflammatory cell recruitment factor in malignant pleural effusion. [CITATION_2] To this end, the authors suggested that these abilities may explain the PF formation.",
